<p>Under tort law there is a <strong>BREACH OF EXPRESS WARRANTY</strong> if a product is sold with 1) <strong>express representations</strong> that the buyer 2) <strong>relies</strong> on and 3) the <strong>representations are incorrect</strong> and 4) it causes the purchaser <strong>injury</strong>. </p>
<p>The seller is liable to foreseeable plaintiffs, those with privity of contract or their family.</p>
